originalText.text: We love the dog sitter nyc! We've had an awesome experience since Sasha started going to daycare and baths 2 months ago. Sasha behaves excitedly the minute she realizes our walk is going to lead us there, it’s very cute, and it lets us know she really loves it there. I wholeheartedly recommend to anyone looking for a great daycare and dog bath in midtown manhattan. I am a fan of places with no kennels where my dog can feel like home, so personally, I really like it!

originalText.text: Been looking for a place for Molly and finally found her ideal place! Molly  loves it there for daycare and boarding. She pulls through the lobby and greets all the people there that take care of her with hugs and kisses each time we go. I love this place and hey have been a life saver, especially because I’ve started traveling for work more now that things have calmed down, and I was afraid Molly wouldn’t be able to adjust to the change, but I am happy to report she has, and she enjoys her time at the dog sitter nyc. I also get sent lots of pics and videos which I appreciate because I am a worrier. Anyway, if you love your dog as much as I do, this is the right place for them.

originalText.text:
From a first time dog owner, I can not thank "The Dog Sitter NYC" enough, they have made this an extremely enjoyable journey for me.
My dog loves coming here!  as soon as we approach the door she starts pulling, it’s crazy. I’m glad she has a place she can go and have fun at. I particularly appreciate their no cages/kennels. I wanted a place for my dog to feel as comfy as if she were home. Really happy about it, and I highly recommend it.
